He tells them to build a hut whose site has been approved, where no harm will be done, and which has a space on all sides.
If they build a hut whose site has not been approved, where harm will be done, and which lacks a space on all sides, the builders commit three offenses of wrong conduct. …
where harm will be done, but which has a space on all sides, the builders commit two offenses of wrong conduct. …
where no harm will be done, but which lacks a space on all sides, the builders commit two offenses of wrong conduct. …
where no harm will be done, and which has a space on all sides, the builders commit one offense of wrong conduct.
