A monk appoints someone to build him a hut and then departs.
They build a hut whose site has not been approved, where harm will be done, and which lacks a space on all sides.
If it is unfinished when he returns, that hut is to be given to someone else, or it is to be demolished and rebuilt.
If he does not give it to someone else, or does not demolish and rebuild it, he commits one offense entailing suspension and two offenses of wrong conduct.
